[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pep Clotet: Leeds United appoint Spaniard as Garry Monk's assistant

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Leeds United have appointed Pep Clotet as head coach Garry Monk's assistant, while Darryl Flahavan has been appointed goalkeeping coach.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Clotet, 39, was also Monk's number two during his time in charge of Swansea.
The Spaniard, who has also coached in his homeland and Sweden, was linked with the head coach's job at Brentford last November.
Flahavan, 37, is taking up his first coaching position after spells with Southend and Bournemouth.
